The sad case of Clement VVriter, who hath waited for reliefe therein since the fourth of Decemb. 1640. Writer, Clement, fl. 1627-1658.
7, [1] p.
s.n., [London : 1653]
Caption title. Imprint from Wing. Includes "To the .. House of Commons for petitions" signed: Alexander Rigby amd Luke Robinson (referrees); and "To the Parliament .. the .. petition of Clement Writer.". The text complains of unjust proceedings by the Lord Keeper Coventry, in the cause of Writer against Worfield. Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
